<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFE7FFD8FF71FDB8FF1DFCF3" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFE7FFD8FF71FDB8FE1AFD2B" blockId="15.[151,1437,582,861]" box="[151,487,618,645]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFE7FFD8FF79FDB8FF14FD2A" box="[159,233,618,644]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[256,1329,189,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-19@61.[247,1340,181,1929]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 8. Eudocima kinabaluenis and Eudocima homaena group adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605514/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 8</figureCitation>
: K, 23: P–Q, 94: D–F)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFE7FFD8FF71FD5CFF1DFCF3" blockId="15.[151,1437,582,861]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
The longitudinal green forewing mark is more irregular than in 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE7FFD8FCBAFD5DFBE8FD06" box="[860,1045,654,681]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kinabaluensis">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE7FFD8FCBAFD5DFC90FD06" box="[860,877,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE7FFD8FC9DFD5CFBE8FD06" box="[891,1045,654,680]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">kinabaluensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE7FFD8FBDCFD5DFB3DFD06" baseAuthorityName="Hubner" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[1082,1216,654,680]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="homaena">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE7FFD8FBDCFD5DFB3DFD06" box="[1082,1216,654,680]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">E. homaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE7FFD8FAECFD5DFF32FD62" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smaragdipicta">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE7FFD8FAECFD5DFF32FD62" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">E. smaragdipicta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE7FFD8FEE5FD61FE75FD62" baseAuthorityName="Hubner" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[259,392,690,716]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="homaena">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE7FFD8FEE5FD61FE75FD62" box="[259,392,690,716]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">E. homaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a medial patch which is lacking in the 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE7FFD8FC8AFD61FBD9FD62" box="[876,1060,690,716]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kinabaluensis">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE7FFD8FC8AFD61FBD9FD62" box="[876,1060,690,716]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">E. kinabaluensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. The life cycle is illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFE7FFD8FF5CFD05FEAEFD5E" author="Leong, T. M." box="[186,339,726,753]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="177 - 182" refId="ref38811" refString="Leong, T. M. (2009) Final Instar Caterpillar and Metamorphosis of Eudocima smaragdipicta (Walker) (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae: Calpinae). Nature in Singapore, 2, 177 - 182." type="journal article" year="2009">Leong (2009)</bibRefCitation>
who found the larvae in 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE7FFD8FD8CFD04FD21FD5E" box="[618,732,726,752]" name="Singapore" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Singapore</collectingCountry>
feeding on 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE7FFD8FC86FD04FBC4FD5E" box="[864,1081,726,752]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Menispermaceae" genus="Fibraurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tinctoria">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE7FFD8FC86FD04FBC4FD5E" box="[864,1081,726,752]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fibraurea tinctoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE7FFD8FBAEFD04FAF0FD5F" baseAuthorityName="Zaspel" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[1096,1293,726,753]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Menispermaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Menispermaceae</taxonomicName>
). That larvae attained a length of 
<quantity id="A21252CFFFE7FFD8FE9CFD28FE31FCBB" box="[378,460,762,789]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="75.0">75 mm</quantity>
, and while resting adopted a typical 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE7FFD8FC88FD28FC1DFCBA" box="[878,992,762,788]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE7FFD8FC88FD28FC1DFCBA" box="[878,992,762,788]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Eudocima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
defensive posture presenting a striking pair of ocelli on the third abdominal segment. It is found in peninsular 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE7FFD8FC5FFCCCFBDFFC96" box="[953,1058,798,824]" name="Malaysia" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, Sumatra, and Borneo (
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFE7FFD8FACAFCCCFF29FCF3" author="Holloway, J. D." pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 529" refId="ref38189" refString="Holloway, J. D. (2005) The moths of Borneo (parts 15 and 16): family Noctuidae, subfamily Catocalinae. Malayan Nature Journal, 59 (1 - 4), 1 - 529." type="journal article" year="2005">Holloway 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
